// Security: DILITHIUM Digital Signature
// ==============================================================================
// This file demonstrates Post-Quantum Cryptographic (PQC) signing.
//
// Key Concepts:
// 1. NIST DILITHIUM: A lattice-based digital signature scheme secure against quantum attacks.
// 2. Statement Integrity: Using #sign directive to prove authorship.
// 3. Non-Repudiation: The agent cannot deny creating this statement.
// ==============================================================================

@version:"2.7.0"
$$group:post_quantum_crypto

// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// 1. Signed Assertion
// Directive: #sign("agent-id") generates a cryptographic signature for the following block.
// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#sign("gpt-4-instance-001")
!Assert {
  <AI> [proved] <RiemannHypothesis> {
    confidence: 0.85,
    algorithm: "DILITHIUM",
    verification_key: "public_key_string"
  }
} @0.85